result.execSummary:
The defendant Shawn P. Biers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+) [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] case called briefly at 10:37am, and then at 10:49am. 
Defendant Shawn P. Biers in court, in custody, with Attorney Benjamin Lutgen.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
[Real-time transcription display is being provided on the courtroom monitors for Mr. Biers.]

Mr. Biers waives his right to Preliminary Hearing. The Court accepts the waiver and binds him over. 
Service of the Information is admitted; reading is waived. 
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " Guilty " entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified.  The Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #2 and #3.

On Count # 1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Biers on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:
--to undergo AODA assessment, treatment and follow through under the supervision of the Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling as supervised by the Agent
--to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as supervised by the Agent
--to comply with all Family Court Orders regarding child support
--to make all child support payments on time 
--to make all payments on arrearages according to the Child Support Order
--all payments towards child support and arrearages will be paid through the Wisconsin Support Collection Trust Fund, Box 74200, Milwaukee WI 53274-0200 , and not through the Department of Corrections 
--within five days Mr. Biers is to report to the Child Support Agency at the Jefferson County Courthouse to complete case management
--Mr. Biers is to advise the Child Support Agency of any employment or address change within 48 hours of such a change 
--to comply with DNA sample provision 

Separate from the conditions of Probation, the Court orders payment of costs, fees and surcharges through the Clerk of Courts Office. [Clerk calculates this total to be: $2,351.97 which includes the $1,833.97 in extradition fees which is listed on the Criminal Case Settlement form] The Court grants the Defendant sixty days to either pay the amount in full or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office.  Non-payment will result in 60 days in Jail with Huber privileges, consecutive.

Days credit for time already served:  95  days
Felony firearm prohibition warnings are given
